Miller Family 
Jill is the primary budget manager for a busy household of six, balancing a full-time career with the complex logistics of raising four children. She is married to Jack who is a mechanic that works long hours. She views her family’s finances as an important detail to keeping the family running smoothly. With children ranging from preschool to high school—all of which are heavily involved in competitive sports her daily focus is on tracking high-volume expenses like groceries, school fees, and utility costs that can quickly scale up in a large home.
With a strong background in data and technology, Jill prefers clear, visual representations over dense spreadsheets. She is interested in a visualization to identify issues in the family budget, such as unnecessary subscriptions or small, fragmented convenience purchases that accumulate over time. Her goal is to keep the household system running smoothly while setting aside resources for major future goals, like an upcoming move to a new city. It is also important that she can share the information easily with her husband. So wants to ensure that there is a seamless way to track spending, so she or Jack can quickly review the budget and ensure that the family's financial storage is used for what matters most 

